categories.summary: The buyer initially expresses feeling lost and unable to navigate the system independently. The buyer encounters difficulties adding data sources, specifically Facebook and Instagram pages, and expresses frustration with the process. The buyer reports that the system is not accepting the LinkedIn page.

The buyer expresses a concern about the timing of setting up campaigns, suggesting it might be quicker to do it themselves. The buyer also indicates they may need help with setting up campaigns, showing a lack of confidence in their ability to do it independently.
The buyer mentions Olivia Taylor in relation to Facebook and LinkedIn connections, suggesting she may be a stakeholder or user of the platform.
The buyer is considering the timing of setting up a campaign, indicating a need to balance internal resources and external support.

summary.text: This appears to be a training call where Alexander Chen (representing the seller) guides Olivia Taylor (the buyer) on using a social media tracking platform. Olivia was having trouble adding Facebook and Instagram data sources; Alexander explained that Facebook requires the full URL while Instagram only needs the account name (after removing the base URL). Alexander demonstrated how to properly input the information and track the accounts. Olivia then inquired about LinkedIn, and Alexander clarified that only owned business pages can be tracked, adding Select Marketing's page for her. Olivia asked about setting up campaigns for specific clients using hashtags and socials; Alexander confirmed this was possible, offering to set it up, but also explaining how Olivia could create and save searches/dashboards herself. Next steps include Olivia potentially setting up dashboards for specific campaigns, and reaching out for help if needed.

items.original_text: Olivia to try adding Instagram accounts, remembering to only use the account name, not the full link.
Olivia to create dashboards for marketing campaigns, using relevant hashtags, taglines, and social media accounts.
Alexander to provide assistance to Olivia if needed when she sets up the marketing campaign dashboards.
